Paper: hep-th/0101183

Date: 2001-01-26

Title: Supersymmetry in Quantum Mechanics of Colored Particles

Authors: Sh. Mamedov, Jian-Zu Zhang and V. Zhukovskii

Comments: 8 pages, no figures

Journal-ref: Mod.Phys.Lett. A16 (2001) 845-852

The role of supercharge operators is studied in the case of a Dirac particlemoving in a constant chromomagnetic field. The Hamiltonian is factorised andthe ground state wave function in the case of unbroken supersymmetry isdetermined.